ond Bulldogs|Richmond Rovers]]\n|13||11||0||2||257||108||'''22'''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Newton Rangers]]\n|13||8||0||5||167||110||'''16'''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby United]]\n|13||7||0||6||139||142||'''14'''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[North Shore Albions|Devonport United]]\n|13||5||1||7||100||130||'''11'''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[City Rovers]]\n|13||4||0||9||145||246||'''8'''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Marist Saints|Marist Old Boys]]\n|13||3||1||9||126||197||'''7'''\n|-\n|}\n\n===Senior Grade Fixtures===\nIn Round 1 C. Allen of [[Newton Rangers]] was ordered off for kicking a [[Richmond Bulldogs|Richmond Rovers]] player and was suspended for two playing Saturday\u2019s.<ref>{{cite news \n| title =Auckland Affairs/Sub-League Formed at Tuakau\n| page = 15\n| work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=LXV| issue=103\n| date = 1934-05-03\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19340503.2.148\n| accessdate = 2019-12-03}}</ref> The new grandstand at Carlaw Park was opened on May 12 along with the Round 3 matches in front of an enormous attendance of 17,000.<ref name=\"league_grandstand\" /> Round 6 saw one match played on the Monday which was a public holiday. The match was between City and Devonport. Round 10 saw the return of Roy Hardgrave to the Newton side after several seasons playing professionally in England.\n\nIt was decided after Round 13 to cease the championship and crown Richmond champions as they were 6 points clear and embarking on a southern tour rendering any further matches meaningless in terms of deciding the title.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable mw-collapsible\"\n|+ class=\"nowrap\" | 1934 Senior Results\n|-\n|\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n! scope=\"col\" | \n! scope=\"col\" | Score\n! scope=\"col\" | \n! scope=\"col\" | Score\n! scope=\"col\" | Venue\n! scope=\"col\" | Attendance\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Round 1\n| 28 April <ref>{{cite news \n| title =The League Code/Opening of the Season/City Defeats Devonport/Second Spell Recovery\n| page = 13\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LXXI| issue=21787\n| date = 1934-04-30\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19340430.2.168.3\n| accessdate = 2019-12-03}}</ref>\n|| City || 13 || Devonport || 7 || Carlaw Park # 1, 3pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | -\n| 28 April || Richmond || 18 || Newton || 7 || Carlaw Park # 1, 1:30pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | -\n| 28 April || Ponsonby || 28 || Marist || 8 || Carlaw Park # 2, 3pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Round 2\n| 5 May <ref>{{cite news \n| title =Second Auckland Series/Newton\u2019s Surprise Victory/Richmond and Ponsonby Again\n| page = 12\n| work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=LXV| issue=106\n| date = 1934-05-07\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19340507.2.137\n| accessdate = 2019-12-03}}</ref>\n|| Ponsonby || 17 || Devonport || 2 || Carlaw Park # 1, 3pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | -\n| 5 May || Newton || 32 || City || 3 || Carlaw Park # 1, 1:30pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | -\n| 5 May || Richmond || 29 || Marist || 3 || Carlaw Park # 2, 3pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Round 3\n| 12 May <ref name=\"auck_champs\" /><ref name=\"league_grandstand\" />\n|| Richmond || 16 || Ponsonby || 4 || Carlaw Park # 1, 3pm||17,000 * ground record for club matches\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | -\n| 12 May || City || 18 || Marist || 5 || Carlaw Park # 1, 1:30pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | -\n| 12 May || Newton || 18 || Devonport || 8 || Carlaw Park # 2, 1:30pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Round 4\n| 19 May <ref>{{cite news \n| title =Richmond Beats City/High-Scoring Contest/First Win For Marist\n| page = 14\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LXXI| issue=21805\n| date = 1934-05-21\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19340521.2.166.6\n| accessdate = 2019-12-04}}</ref>\n|| Richmond || 46 || City || 16 || Carlaw Park # 1, 3pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | -\n| 19 May || Ponsonby || 8 || Newton || 5 || Carlaw Park # 1, 1:30pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | -\n| 19 May || Marist |